{"NAMABLE":[{"def":"Capable of being named.","pos":""}],"NAMATION":[{"def":"A distraining or levying of a distress; an impounding.","pos":""}],"NAMAYCUSH":[{"def":"A large North American lake trout (Salvelinus namaycush).","pos":""}],"NAMBY-PAMBY":[{"def":"Talk or writing which is weakly sentimental or affectedly pretty.","pos":""}],"NAME":[{"def":"The title by which any person or thing is known or designated; a distinctive specific appellation, whether of an individual or a class.","pos":""},{"def":"A descriptive or qualifying appellation given to a person or thing, on account of a character or acts.","pos":""}],"NAMELESS":[{"def":"Without a name; not having been given a name; as, a nameless star.","pos":""},{"def":"Undistinguished; not noted or famous.","pos":""}],"NAMELESSLY":[{"def":"In a nameless manner.","pos":""}],"NAMELY":[{"def":"By name; by particular mention; specifically; especially; expressly.","pos":""},{"def":"That is to say; to wit; videlicet; -- introducing a particular or specific designation.","pos":""}],"NAMER":[{"def":"One who names, or calls by name.","pos":""}],"NAMESAKE":[{"def":"One that has the same name as another; especially, one called after, or named out of regard to, another.","pos":""}]}